OL,4,Cwith hatchet outside police station
OL,6,FThe judge said it is clear that
OL,7,FDighton "continue(s) to hold
OL,8,Fentrenched views" and that he had been
OL,9,Freported to Prevent on the basis of
OL,10,Fracist and anti-Muslim views, and
OL,11,Flikelihood of being involved with
OL,12,Fincel groups.
OL,14,FIn a sentencing hearing at The Old
OL,15,FBailey today (13 June), the court
OL,16,Fheard that Dighton, of Llantrisant,
OL,17,FRhondda Cynon Taf, arrived at the
OL,18,Fpolice station shortly before 7pm,
OL,19,Fwhere he lit a petrol bomb and threw
OL,20,Fit at a police van.
