OL,7,FDighton to life imprisonment and
OL,8,Fordered him to serve a minimum of 22
OL,9,Fyears.
OL,11,FThe judge told the defendant that the
OL,12,Foffences had "a terrorist connection",
OL,13,Fsaying: "It is clear that you continue
OL,14,Fto hold entrenched views."
OL,16,F"Other than the early guilty pleas,
OL,17,Fthere is little else to be said to
OL,18,Fyour credit."
